26,349 Likes
Midjourney, the company you know for turning text into images, just announc=
ed
Midjourney Medical
, a full-body scanner. Nobody saw this coming.
Here is what it actually is. You step into a pool of water. Sound waves pas=
s through your body from every angle.
60 seconds later
, you have a 3D map of your entire body. No radiation, no magnets, just ult=
rasound.
The specs are wild:
500,000 transducers
(tiny sensors) firing sound waves through you simultaneously
17 gigabytes of data processed every second
A few dollars per scan, not hundreds
First location opens in a San Francisco spa in 2027
The goal is catching health problems early, before symptoms show up. Think =
of it like version control for your body , scan regularly, spot changes ove=
r time.
They are starting with body composition data (fat, muscle, bone density) wh=
ile working toward FDA approval for full diagnostics. Midjourney has never =
shipped a physical product before, so the 2027 timeline is the real test.
