<p>Midjourney, the company you know for turning text into images, just anno=
unced <b>Midjourney Medical</b> , a full-body scanner. Nobody saw this comi=
ng.</p><p>Here is what it actually is. You step into a pool of water. Sound=
 waves pass through your body from every angle. <b>60 seconds later</b>, yo=
u have a 3D map of your entire body. No radiation, no magnets, just ultraso=
und.</p><p>The specs are wild:</p><ul><li><b>500,000 transducers</b> (tiny =
sensors) firing sound waves through you simultaneously</li><li>17 gigabytes=
 of data processed every second</li><li>A few dollars per scan, not hundred=
s</li><li>First location opens in a San Francisco spa in 2027</li></ul><p>T=
he goal is catching health problems early, before symptoms show up. Think o=
f it like version control for your body , scan regularly, spot changes over=
 time.</p><p>They are starting with body composition data (fat, muscle, bon=
e density) while working toward FDA approval for full diagnostics. Midjourn=
ey has never shipped a physical product before, so the 2027 timeline is the=
 real test.</p>
